Message: Please direct me to creatives dimensions guide for image and video ads

Sure thing! For image and video ads, NewsBreak supports both vertical and horizontal formats. Images should be in 9x16 (vertical) or 16x9 (horizontal), while videos can also be in these dimensions. You can find more detailed information on creative best practices and A/B testing in this article: [Creative Best Practices](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/20676690598029-Ad-Creative-Best-Practices-and-A-B-Testing).
Hello I just updated the destination urls in the ads in my Mitolyn 2 campaign. Same destination lander but I modified to use the proper Voluum campaign url. I'd apprecaite a quick review thank you.

Hi there! It sounds like you've updated your destination URLs to use the correct Voluum campaign URL. To ensure everything is set up correctly, you can follow these steps:
1. Double-check that the Voluum tracking URL is correctly implemented in your NewsBreak campaign.
2. Make sure that all necessary macros and parameters are appended to the URL for accurate tracking.
3. Test the postback integration in NewsBreak's Event Manager to confirm that conversions are being recorded properly.
For detailed guidance, you can refer to this article on setting up a Voluum Postback with NewsBreak: [How to set up a Voluum Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/24825901083277-How-to-set-up-a-Voluum-Postback-on-NewsBreak).
If you have any specific questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!

To clone a campaign on NewsBreak, you can follow these general steps: 
1. Go to your Ad Management dashboard.
2. Find the campaign you want to clone.
3. Click on the 'Actions' button next to the campaign.
4. Select 'Clone' from the dropdown menu.
5. Make any necessary adjustments to the cloned campaign settings, such as budget or targeting.
6. Save your changes and launch the cloned campaign.
For more detailed instructions, please refer to our Campaign Set-Up Guide here: [Campaign Set-Up Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/29943576259469-Campaign-Set-Up-Guide).
